Articles.Content:
Hi, it's not problem for me to download this mod manualy and install, but can u update CKAN metadata to newest version? Or is this done by CKAN team? Sorry...I'm a bit new at things which handle CKAN team and which developers...

Ave!

Toonu

1.4.4 

- fix a memory use related to the FPS/Memory displays that @Padishar detected a long teim ago but I could not track down before;

Download : GCMonitor-1.4.4.0.zip

(And updated the .version so CKAN should follow soonish)

1.4.4 

- fix the config button....

Download : GCMonitor-1.4.5.0.zip

The GCMonitor.cfg is no longer created and stored, resulting in default font size and position on each game launch regardless of applied settings in a game session. Copying over a config from previous version works fine. 1.1.3, RP-0 suite, output log.

Edited July 13, 2016 by Ixenzo

Thanks for your great work here. I enyou many of your mods.

But there is a little Problem between GCMonitor and ModuleManager. If you use the ReloadDatabase-Funktion then starts an new Instance of GCMonitor. There is no Check if GCMonitor already run.

I woukld like to ask, if the actual GCmonitor works on MAC too.

If I use it, I get FPS-data, but no memory-information.

14 minutes ago, Isabelle.V.Fuchs said:

I woukld like to ask, if the actual GCmonitor works on MAC too.

If I use it, I get FPS-data, but no memory-information.

It worked when I added the feature. I do not have a Mac to test so I don't know if it still does. The log should have some info if there is a problem.

Hi!

 

Since I don't know how to add a file I add the log as 'code'.

I hope I don't spam the topic now :-/
